WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,
obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments
drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line
in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered
the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

13
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!

14
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

15
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

16
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

17
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

18
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

19
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

20
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through

21
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it

22
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

23
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

24
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,

25
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

26
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!

27
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

28
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:56.760
<b>The Second</b>

29
00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:30.960
Is his arm okay?

30
00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:34.470
If he had backed off even
one step, he would've lost it!

31
00:02:34.470 --> 00:02:39.640
I highly doubt he thought about
how shark fangs work.

32
00:02:42.390 --> 00:02:44.690
Is Big Bro's arm okay?

33
00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:57.820
H-Huh?

34
00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:00.120
Where'd he go?

35
00:03:01.290 --> 00:03:02.660
Luffy! The sea!

36
00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:03.500
The sea?

37
00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:07.420
There's a shark!

38
00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:10.630
That's Arlong!

39
00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:15.300
What? Did he dive down?

40
00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:21.350
This is bad! He's even more
powerful in the water!

41
00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:29.860
No one can stop me once
I pick up speed underwater.

42
00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:34.860
This is a prime example of the kind of
power only fishmen are blessed with.

43
00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:37.820
Did he run away?

44
00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:46.330
Shark Gone...

45
00:03:46.330 --> 00:03:48.670
Darts!

46
00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:55.920
What was that?!

47
00:03:56.670 --> 00:03:58.010
A torpedo?!

48
00:04:01.260 --> 00:04:03.970
Something flew out of the water!

49
00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:08.390
Ow...! Ow, ow, ow, ow...

50
00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:16.690
I'm impressed you dodged that.

51
00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:21.700
But the more you dodge,
the longer you'll spend in hell.

52
00:04:22.950 --> 00:04:28.660
Shark Gone Darts!

53
00:04:38.670 --> 00:04:42.640
Wh-What the hell are that
damn shark's bones made of?!

54
00:04:43.470 --> 00:04:45.600
His nose shattered the ground!

55
00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:49.850
Shark Gone Darts!

56
00:05:04.830 --> 00:05:09.290
Hey Luffy, you gotta hide!
He went into the water again!

57
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.580
Big Bro! Hurry up and hide already!

58
00:05:13.580 --> 00:05:15.800
He's gonna come after you again!

59
00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:21.760
Get out of there!

60
00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:26.760
N... No...

61
00:05:27.890 --> 00:05:31.770
Don't be stupid! You're a sitting duck
right now! Take cover!

62
00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:36.770
No way! I'll catch him
and break his damn nose!

63
00:05:37.190 --> 00:05:39.990
Come at me, shark!

64
00:05:43.450 --> 00:05:45.200
You've got some nerve.

65
00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:48.910
Or perhaps you've realized
that running away won't save you?

66
00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:53.540
What part of "hurry up and hide"
don't you understand?!

67
00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:57.550
You couldn't even fully dodge
any of his attacks!

68
00:05:57.550 --> 00:06:01.470
You'll die instantly
if he hits you head-on!

69
00:06:01.470 --> 00:06:03.340
Gum-Gum...

70
00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:08.390
Shield!

71
00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:10.390
What's with that stance?

72
00:06:10.390 --> 00:06:12.350
He's not doing that to block it, is he?

73
00:06:13.310 --> 00:06:15.310
I have twice the room
to pick up speed now!

74
00:06:15.980 --> 00:06:18.480
I'll pierce right through your heart!

75
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:23.110
Shark Gone Darts!

76
00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:30.700
It's a direct hit!

77
00:06:43.510 --> 00:06:45.590
Wait, did he get hit?!

78
00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:48.550
No! He flung himself away!

79
00:06:51.270 --> 00:06:54.480
You lose! That attack
won't work anymore!

80
00:06:54.480 --> 00:06:58.060
Shark Gone Darts!

81
00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:06.200
You bastard! That was
just a lucky guess!

82
00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:07.910
This is the final blow!

83
00:07:08.530 --> 00:07:09.870
Like that's gonna work!

84
00:07:10.280 --> 00:07:11.830
Gum-Gum...

85
00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:13.620
Net!

86
00:07:15.750 --> 00:07:17.750
Fishing! I'm fishing!

87
00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:25.010
And...

88
00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:29.800
Spear!

89
00:07:36.020 --> 00:07:37.900
Holy crap!

90
00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:42.860
Alright, let's go!

91
00:07:43.570 --> 00:07:46.070
Hm? Is he dead?

92
00:07:48.660 --> 00:07:50.490
The look in Arlong's eyes changed!

93
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:54.790
He looks just like the sea kings
when they're pissed off.

94
00:07:55.750 --> 00:07:58.000
Luffy's last attack
must've made him snap!

95
00:08:00.460 --> 00:08:04.420
I've never seen Arlong look like that...

96
00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:07.590
Inferior human!

97
00:08:09.340 --> 00:08:11.510
Who do you think you are...

98
00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:15.220
to raise a hand against a fishman!?

99
00:08:23.320 --> 00:08:25.320
Boy, that caught me by surprise!

100
00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:29.280
It didn't hurt,
but he's definitely pissed.

101
00:08:39.790 --> 00:08:41.420
What the heck is that?

102
00:08:41.790 --> 00:08:43.040
The Shark Saw!

103
00:08:43.040 --> 00:08:45.420
That's a big-ass saw!

104
00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:08.740
Big Bro Luffy!

105
00:09:08.740 --> 00:09:10.360
Hang in there, Luffy!

106
00:09:10.740 --> 00:09:13.370
He just won't let up!
Luffy is gonna get cornered!
Run! Watch out!

107
00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:22.880
He escaped into the building!

108
00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:33.090
The left window on the top floor...

109
00:09:34.430 --> 00:09:36.100
That's the room where...

110
00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:39.480
There's nowhere left to run.

111
00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:44.150
This is the top floor of Arlong Park.

112
00:09:44.650 --> 00:09:46.070
What is this room?

113
00:09:46.650 --> 00:09:48.030
It's full of papers.

114
00:09:48.030 --> 00:09:50.360
They're no ordinary papers.

115
00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:54.490
This room is where I make that
girl draw sea charts. This is...

116
00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:57.490
...the cartography room!

117
00:09:58.330 --> 00:09:59.910
Nami's room...

118
00:09:59.910 --> 00:10:03.830
Nami drew every one
of these sea charts.

119
00:10:05.380 --> 00:10:10.970
How many people in the world do you think can draw charts this accurate?

120
00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:14.430
That girl has a gift.

121
00:10:20.680 --> 00:10:24.060
There's nothing as sad and senseless

122
00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:26.650
as letting natural-born
talent go to waste.

123
00:10:26.650 --> 00:10:32.320
She'll find true happiness
by staying here and drawing charts!

124
00:10:32.320 --> 00:10:36.160
This pen is stained with blood...

125
00:10:36.530 --> 00:10:41.370
These charts are absolutely vital
if I am to achieve world domination!

126
00:10:43.830 --> 00:10:49.420
That girl is going to keep drawing sea
charts, for the sake of my ambition!

127
00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:53.010
Once we've learned everything about
the world's seas from those charts,

128
00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:58.680
we fishmen will reign supreme,
and my empire will span the globe!

129
00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:04.770
This island and the East Blue
are stepping stones toward that end!

130
00:11:07.230 --> 00:11:12.190
How could you possibly use
her as effectively as me?!

131
00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.830
What the...?! My Shark Saw...

132
00:11:23.370 --> 00:11:25.250
isn't budging!

133
00:11:29.290 --> 00:11:30.210
What?!

134
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.420
"Use"?!

135
00:11:35.380 --> 00:11:37.760
What's goin' on in there?!

136
00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:41.510
Dammit... What happened,
Big Bro Luffy?!

137
00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:45.480
I can't tell what's
going on up there at all...

138
00:11:48.730 --> 00:11:49.650
Luffy...

139
00:11:50.940 --> 00:11:53.730
What do you take her for?!

140
00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:59.070
She may be an inferior creature,
but she's a clever girl, too.

141
00:11:59.070 --> 00:12:01.740
If all other humans are sewer rats,

142
00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:04.700
then she's a sassy little cat.

143
00:12:04.700 --> 00:12:06.960
After all, she is adorable.

144
00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:12.420
I'm going to keep on feeding her
and buying her the clothes she likes.

145
00:12:12.420 --> 00:12:16.010
She'll have everything
she needs to live.

146
00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:21.260
All she has to do is keep
drawing charts for me.

147
00:12:23.010 --> 00:12:26.390
She will forever be my tool...

148
00:12:26.390 --> 00:12:27.490
No...

149
00:12:28.200 --> 00:12:29.850
one of us.

150
00:12:38.650 --> 00:12:39.320
What's that?!

151
00:12:42.160 --> 00:12:43.490
A desk...?

152
00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:45.700
It's a desk!

153
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:49.830
Wh-Whew! It's just a desk.

154
00:12:49.830 --> 00:12:53.420
Man, that scared me. I thought
it was Big Bro Luffy for sure...

155
00:12:53.420 --> 00:12:55.250
Hold on, partner!

156
00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:58.380
Are you sayin' you don't have
faith in Big Bro Luffy's strength?!

157
00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:02.340
Wha...?! You were
scared too, Johnny!

158
00:13:02.340 --> 00:13:04.350
D-Don't be stupid!
I was, uh, you know...

159
00:13:04.350 --> 00:13:05.810
Obviously...

160
00:13:05.810 --> 00:13:07.680
Obviously I thought it was Arlong!

161
00:13:07.680 --> 00:13:10.770
Huh?! It sounds like you're
trying to pull one over on me!

162
00:13:10.770 --> 00:13:16.010
What's that, you jerk?! Obviously
Big Bro Luffy would never lose!

163
00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:17.360
Luffy?

164
00:13:19.110 --> 00:13:20.700
What do you think you're doing?!

165
00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:26.370
What the hell is going on?!
Stuff is flying everywhere!

166
00:13:36.050 --> 00:13:39.340
Alright! As of today, this is your room!

167
00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:41.590
Your desk, your pens...

168
00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:44.470
Everything you'll need is here!

169
00:13:48.430 --> 00:13:49.730
Stop that!

170
00:13:51.390 --> 00:13:52.810
The charts!

171
00:13:55.110 --> 00:13:56.150
M-My charts!

172
00:13:59.820 --> 00:14:00.820
You damn brat!

173
00:14:00.820 --> 00:14:02.400
Don't think you can trick me...

174
00:14:03.530 --> 00:14:05.740
drawing fake charts like that!

175
00:14:07.790 --> 00:14:11.210
Do you have the time to be
drawing crap like this in secret?

176
00:14:14.750 --> 00:14:19.300
Pull another stunt like that, and I'll
drag the villagers here one by one

177
00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:22.010
and make you watch
as I snuff out their lives!

178
00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:23.630
They'll meet the same fate she did!

179
00:14:29.220 --> 00:14:31.680
Damn you! I spent eight years
making her draw those!

180
00:14:31.680 --> 00:14:34.650
I invested eight years in
those charts! In my ambition!

181
00:14:39.020 --> 00:14:40.610
Bell-mère...

182
00:14:41.820 --> 00:14:43.570
Nojiko...!

183
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:52.290
This is a pretty intense fight!

184
00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:54.830
Yeah! Looks like a fight to the death!

185
00:14:54.830 --> 00:14:55.790
Definitely!

186
00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:05.630
Thank you...!

187
00:15:11.890 --> 00:15:14.890
You've gone too far, you rubber freak!

188
00:15:16.900 --> 00:15:19.690
"Fishmen are great"...

189
00:15:19.690 --> 00:15:21.400
"sea charts" this,

190
00:15:22.400 --> 00:15:23.610
"circumstances" that...

191
00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:25.950
I don't know much
about any of that stuff...

192
00:15:26.530 --> 00:15:30.780
but I finally figured out
how to save her!

193
00:15:36.500 --> 00:15:39.630
This room is why she
can't leave this place!

194
00:15:39.630 --> 00:15:42.250
It's not a home, it's a prison cell!

195
00:15:42.250 --> 00:15:44.470
I'm gonna tear this place
to the ground!

196
00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:47.340
Gum-Gum...

197
00:15:48.930 --> 00:15:50.550
Don't get cocky!

198
00:15:50.550 --> 00:15:55.140
Scum like you could never
bring down Arlong Park!

199
00:15:55.850 --> 00:15:58.350
Shark...

200
00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:00.480
Tooth Drill!

201
00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:02.520
...Battle Axe!

202
00:16:46.190 --> 00:16:48.900
L-Look at that impact!
Arlong Park is gonna...!

203
00:16:50.610 --> 00:16:51.950
No way! It's gonna collapse!

204
00:16:51.950 --> 00:16:53.580
This is bad! Everyone, get back!

205
00:16:54.830 --> 00:16:56.330
Big Sis Nami! Hurry!

206
00:16:56.330 --> 00:16:57.620
But Luffy's still inside!

207
00:16:57.620 --> 00:16:58.330
Big Sis!

208
00:16:58.330 --> 00:16:59.830
Luffy! What about Luffy?!

209
00:17:05.750 --> 00:17:07.590
Luffy!

210
00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:21.440
Luffy...

211
00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:33.120
Luffy...

212
00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:49.760
Ow... Oww!

213
00:17:49.760 --> 00:17:52.430
What's all this damn noise?

214
00:17:57.640 --> 00:17:58.470
Luffy...

215
00:18:12.200 --> 00:18:15.280
Arlong Park... collapsed!

216
00:18:15.950 --> 00:18:17.030
Big Bro...

217
00:18:17.700 --> 00:18:20.660
What the hell happened in there?

218
00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:23.290
Who won?!

219
00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:26.630
Given all this debris...
Don't tell me it was...!

220
00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:29.300
Luffy...

221
00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:41.020
Luffy!

222
00:18:41.020 --> 00:18:44.850
– Big Bro!
– Big Bro!

223
00:18:48.900 --> 00:18:51.610
Is he okay?!

224
00:18:57.620 --> 00:18:59.870
Nami!

225
00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:08.960
You're one of us!

226
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:22.640
Yeah!

227
00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:36.030
More feelings than I can hold but I can’t make you understand

228
00:19:36.050 --> 00:19:40.890
Be that as it may, I just can’t bear to let go of your hand

229
00:19:40.940 --> 00:19:45.840
I’ve still gotta move, even if I’m alone I’ll walk along

230
00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:51.110
Just promise that you’ll still keep 
an eye on me when I am gone

231
00:19:55.760 --> 00:20:00.640
As soon as I woke up, couldn’t get it off my mind

232
00:20:00.690 --> 00:20:05.390
“Why the hell’s it so hot? I can hardly breathe!”

233
00:20:05.390 --> 00:20:11.900
It’s been quite a while, 
but those thoughts just won’t seem to let go

234
00:20:11.900 --> 00:20:15.780
But hey, what do I know?

235
00:20:16.730 --> 00:20:21.640
Guess I want a taste of that thing people call a “runner’s high”

236
00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:26.520
Think I chased too hard, and ended up leaving myself behind

237
00:20:26.570 --> 00:20:31.500
All I want’s a taste of a dream that a sentence can’t define

238
00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:36.700
Stick right by my side, and I can run, run, run until I die
